docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Oct. 31.--A continuation of the depressed economic conditions in many foreign countries, with some indications of improvement in Canada, the Dutch East Indies, the Philippine Islands and Sweden, was indicated in a survey of twenty-four countries, made public today by the Department of Commerce.
